00:49:55.750 --> 00:49:57.250
AUDIENCE: In "Magic--
the Gathering"

00:49:57.250 --> 00:49:58.624
there was a push
in the late '90s

00:49:58.624 --> 00:50:00.790
to make the game more
like, this is for boys,

00:50:00.790 --> 00:50:03.370
and we're going to take all
that art we did in early '90s

00:50:03.370 --> 00:50:04.540
with all the women
in it, and now it's

00:50:04.540 --> 00:50:06.706
all going to be chain mail
bikinis from here on out.

00:50:06.706 --> 00:50:08.900
Was there a similar reaction
sort of phase in "D&amp;D?"

00:50:08.900 --> 00:50:10.530
Where they pushed
against, sort of,

00:50:10.530 --> 00:50:13.240
and then swung
back the other way?

00:50:13.240 --> 00:50:16.060
JON PETERSON: I think when
Wizards acquired TSR and did

00:50:16.060 --> 00:50:18.760
Third Edition, there
was a very decided push

00:50:18.760 --> 00:50:21.389
to be more inclusive and
to show figures like--

00:50:21.389 --> 00:50:22.930
they had these iconic
characters they

00:50:22.930 --> 00:50:24.280
used to represent the classes.

00:50:24.280 --> 00:50:28.660
The monk class was represented
by Ember, who is female--

00:50:28.660 --> 00:50:30.070
a woman of color.

00:50:30.070 --> 00:50:32.350
I think they really made
a big push around it then

00:50:32.350 --> 00:50:35.410
and they also made a push to
try to make armor look more

00:50:35.410 --> 00:50:37.707
like it would look
in-universe if it were real.

00:50:37.707 --> 00:50:39.790
Which was kind of a reaction
against the more high

00:50:39.790 --> 00:50:42.630
fantasy-ish art of the 1980s.

00:50:42.630 --> 00:50:45.340
I think since then they've been
pretty good about this stuff,

00:50:45.340 --> 00:50:45.840
right?

00:50:45.840 --> 00:50:47.280
I mean certainly Fifth.

00:50:47.280 --> 00:50:49.570
These people have
absolutely no patience.

00:50:49.570 --> 00:50:51.029
People like Mike
Morales, who you

00:50:51.029 --> 00:50:52.570
see in one of the
leads on Fifth now,

00:50:52.570 --> 00:50:54.985
has no patience for anyone
who's trying to exclude anyone

00:50:54.985 --> 00:50:55.610
from this game.

00:50:55.610 --> 00:50:57.400
MICHAEL WITWER:
Absolutely right.

00:50:57.400 --> 00:50:58.240
One more question.

00:50:58.240 --> 00:50:59.560
JON PETERSON: One more thing.

